column1: # Caller = The algorithm used to identify the fusion.
# Gene A = The gene associated with the A side of the fusion. A semicolon delimited list will be used for multiple genes.
# Gene B = The gene associated with the B side of the fusion. A semicolon delimited list will be used for multiple genes.
# Gene A Breakpoint = The chromosome and offset of the Gene A side of the fusion.
# Gene B Breakpoint = The chromosome and offset of the Gene B side of the fusion.
# Score = The quality of fusion as determined by the respective caller. Results from different callers are not equivalent.
# Filter = The filter associated with the fusion as determined by the respective caller. Results from different callers are not equivalent.
# Precise/Imprecise = Whether the algorithm could identify the precise fusion coordinates. Coordinates listed for imprecise fusions are based on strongest statistical evidence. (RFF Only)
# Intragenic Call = List any genes associated with a splice overlapping the fusion. A semicolon delimited list will be used for multiple genes. (SG Only)
# Ref A Split = Gene A uniquely mapping reads spanning the junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads included.

column1: # Ref A Pair = Gene A uniquely mapping reads paired across junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads included.

column1: # Ref B Split = Gene B uniquely mapping reads spanning the junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads included.

column1: # Ref B Pair = Gene B uniquely mapping reads paired across junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads included.

column1: # Alt Split = Uniquely mapping reads split by the junction
# Alt Pair = Uniquely mapping reads paired across junction
# Contig = Sequence of fusion. Can be used to determine fusion directionality (RFF Only)
# ContigAlign1 = Length of Gene A in contig (RFF Only)
# ContigAlign2 = Length of Gene B in contig (RFF Only)
# CandidateAlt = The number of reads and pairs that potentially supports this candidate before refinement and scoring. (RFF Imprecise Reads Only)
# KeepFusion = The determination whether the fusion should be kept or dropped from the list of fusions.
# Ref A Dedup = Gene A uniquely mapping reads paired across or split by the junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads are not included.

column1: # Ref B Dedup = Gene B uniquely mapping reads paired across or split by the junction
column2: does not support fusion. Duplicate reads are not included.

column1: # Alt Split Dedup = Uniquely mapping reads split by the junction
column2: supports fusion. Duplicate reads are not included.

column1: # Alt Pair Dedup = Uniquely mapping reads paired across junction
column2: supports fusion. Duplicate reads are not included.

column1: # Fusion Directionality Known = Whether Fusion Directionality is known and indicated by gene order.
